    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<p>Senior grain factor, Loftwick. Mid-fifties — tall, capable, dark hair gone iron-gray at the temples. Wears a dark green merchant's overdress, brass measuring key on a cord at her hip. Twelve years in independent trade; before that, she clerked for the Loftwick Treasury's Grain Office.</p><p>Her counting house is on Tannerway, near the eastern caravan yard. Husband: Vellin Moraven (schoolmaster). Eldest daughter: Ailen Moraven (mid-twenties, studying with a sculptor in Hardby — tuition co-sponsored by Tamsin and Trina Alvere).</p><p>She was pulling at Cindren &amp; Vhal's false harvest-receipts — claims filed before the losses occurred, by eleven days in one case. Then she walked out of her counting house with a bag and a heavy cloak, told her staff she was riding to a customer's farm, and did not come back. She left one note for Vellin: <em>If I am not back by Sevenday, take Ailen out of Hardby.</em> She knew she was in danger and went anyway.</p><p><strong>Status in Phase 2:</strong> Alive, in Hardby. The ledger fragment reads MORAVEN <em>delayed</em> — not settled. She is on a clock.</p>",
        "public": ""
      },
